Hey, Professor.

265
00:25:03,795 --> 00:25:04,920
Hello.

266
00:25:05,004 --> 00:25:07,130
Here, please.

267
00:25:07,215 --> 00:25:08,799
I need help.

268
00:25:10,802 --> 00:25:12,260
Just be honest.

269
00:25:12,387 --> 00:25:13,553
How bad is it?

270
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:17,265
I think your insights here
are persuasive, but...

271
00:25:20,812 --> 00:25:22,771
Have you been to the river?

272
00:25:37,120 --> 00:25:38,453
Mafalda!

273
00:25:39,038 --> 00:25:40,372
Isn't she beautiful?

274
00:26:00,017 --> 00:26:01,268
Elio.

275
00:26:02,478 --> 00:26:03,979
You sleeping?

276
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:06,773
I was.

277
00:26:06,858 --> 00:26:09,526
Listen to this drivel.
Tell me what you think.

278
00:26:10,403 --> 00:26:12,821
- Wait.
- What?

279
00:26:12,905 --> 00:26:14,614
Can't hear you.

280
00:26:23,708 --> 00:26:25,542
"For the early Greeks,

281
00:26:25,626 --> 00:26:27,252
"Heidegger contends,
this underlying hiddenness

282
00:26:27,336 --> 00:26:29,129
"is constitutive of the way beings are,

283
00:26:29,213 --> 00:26:30,547
"not only in relation to themselves

284
00:26:30,631 --> 00:26:33,258
"but also in relation
to other entities generally.

285
00:26:33,342 --> 00:26:35,051
"In other words,
they do not construe hiddenness

286
00:26:35,136 --> 00:26:38,638
"merely or primarily in terms of
entities' relations to human beings."

287
00:26:40,016 --> 00:26:42,058
Does that make any sense to you?

288
00:26:42,143 --> 00:26:44,519
Doesn't make any sense to me.

289
00:26:44,604 --> 00:26:46,563
I don't think it makes
any sense to your dad, either.

290
00:26:47,899 --> 00:26:49,608
Maybe it did when you wrote it.

291
00:26:54,572 --> 00:26:57,407
That might be the kindest thing
anybody has said to me in months.

292
00:26:58,117 --> 00:27:00,118
"Kind"?

293
00:27:00,203 --> 00:27:02,204
Yep. Kind.

294
00:27:27,855 --> 00:27:31,066
- Hey, Elio.
- Hey.

295
00:27:31,150 --> 00:27:32,526
Hey!

296
00:27:35,363 --> 00:27:36,530
Come here.

297
00:27:38,866 --> 00:27:40,283
What's going on?

298
00:27:40,368 --> 00:27:42,160
Is he trying to get it on with her?

299
00:27:42,286 --> 00:27:44,412
Elio, he already succeeded?

300
00:27:46,332 --> 00:27:47,749
What do I know?

301
00:27:47,834 --> 00:27:49,501
I'd love to be in his shoes.

302
00:27:49,585 --> 00:27:51,503
Who wouldn't love to be in her shoes?

303
00:27:53,965 --> 00:27:56,216
She wants him, no matter what!

304
00:28:40,469 --> 00:28:41,636
Coming?

305
00:28:43,973 --> 00:28:45,307
I'll come later.

306
00:30:00,716 --> 00:30:03,593
Are you with me because
you're mad at Chiara?

307
00:30:03,678 --> 00:30:05,345
Why would I be mad at Chiara?

308
00:30:06,555 --> 00:30:08,056
Because of him.

309
00:30:08,140 --> 00:30:09,599
Because of who?

310
00:30:10,768 --> 00:30:12,018
Of Oliver.

311
00:30:23,531 --> 00:30:24,906
Turn around.

312
00:30:39,547 --> 00:30:41,381
Meet me here tomorrow night?

313
00:30:48,264 --> 00:30:50,557
Wait for me!

314
00:30:50,641 --> 00:30:52,183
Come on.

315
00:31:05,614 --> 00:31:07,615
We almost had sex last night...

316
00:31:07,700 --> 00:31:10,076
Marzia and me.

317
00:31:11,871 --> 00:31:13,580
Well, why didn't you?

318
00:31:14,373 --> 00:31:15,874
I don't know.

319
00:31:17,001 --> 00:31:19,711
Well, you know, it's better
to have tried and failed, right?

320
00:31:19,795 --> 00:31:23,590
All I had to do was find the courage
to reach out and touch.

321
00:31:23,674 --> 00:31:25,216
She would have said yes.

322
00:31:25,301 --> 00:31:27,052
Well, try again later.

323
00:31:27,178 --> 00:31:28,928
Try what later?

324
00:31:29,013 --> 00:31:30,680
I just heard
from the people in Sirmione.

325
00:31:30,765 --> 00:31:32,599
They say they've come up with something.

326
00:31:32,683 --> 00:31:34,976
Fantastic.

327
00:31:35,061 --> 00:31:36,603
Going there today.

328
00:31:36,687 --> 00:31:39,022
- Would you like to come along?
- I would love to. Thank you.

329
00:31:40,566 --> 00:31:42,609
- Smell this.
- Can I come, too?

330
00:31:42,693 --> 00:31:45,278
On the condition you remain silent.

331
00:31:45,905 --> 00:31:47,197
Silent as in,
"He has too many opinions,"

332
00:31:47,281 --> 00:31:48,865
or silent as in,
"Just not telling anybody

333
00:31:48,949 --> 00:31:50,617
"what an amazing thing you've dug up"?

334
00:31:50,701 --> 00:31:52,243
Well, nothing has been dug up.

335
00:31:52,328 --> 00:31:54,954
It's what has been brought out,
out of the water.

336
00:32:03,714 --> 00:32:05,173
What are you doing?

337
00:32:05,299 --> 00:32:07,217
Going to Lake Garda with my dad.

338
00:32:07,301 --> 00:32:09,302
He wants to show Oliver
where he's dredging.

339
00:32:10,262 --> 00:32:11,638
Can you tell him I came by?

340
00:32:12,598 --> 00:32:14,474
He's inside with my dad, helping him.

341
00:32:16,310 --> 00:32:19,729
You were amazing last night,
on the dance floor.

342
00:32:19,814 --> 00:32:21,689
- He's a good dancer.
- A good dancer.

343
00:32:24,068 --> 00:32:25,735
He's good-looking too.

344
00:32:27,196 --> 00:32:28,988
- Want to get us together?
- No.

345
00:32:30,741 --> 00:32:32,408
Come in.

346
00:33:09,155 --> 00:33:11,698
Dad always sits up front
with Anchise to navigate.

347
00:33:19,290 --> 00:33:21,749
She seems to like you a lot.

348
00:33:21,834 --> 00:33:24,502
She's more beautiful
than she was last year.

349
00:33:25,921 --> 00:33:29,382
I saw her naked on a night swim once.

350
00:33:29,466 --> 00:33:31,426
Great body.

351
00:33:31,594 --> 00:33:33,178
Trying to get me to like her?

352
00:33:33,304 --> 00:33:35,346
What would be the harm in that?

353
00:33:35,472 --> 00:33:36,639
No, no harm.

354
00:33:36,724 --> 00:33:38,766
Just typically like to go at those
things on my own, if you don't mind.

355
00:33:43,689 --> 00:33:44,939
I'll drive today!

356
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:51,321
Just don't play at being the good host.

357
00:33:53,199 --> 00:33:56,618
Anchise, take the afternoon off.

358
00:33:58,913 --> 00:34:00,455
What's going on, boys?

359
00:34:01,707 --> 00:34:07,086
Oliver, come. Sit up front.
Be my navigator.

360
00:34:07,171 --> 00:34:09,631
What? What?

361
00:34:24,688 --> 00:34:26,856
- Dr. Roseburg.
- Samuel!

362
00:34:26,941 --> 00:34:28,900
- Benvenuto.
- Look who's here.

363
00:34:30,486 --> 00:34:32,237
- He's grown a bit, eh?
- And this is Oliver.

364
00:35:01,767 --> 00:35:03,518
Sammy! Come on!

365
00:35:16,573 --> 00:35:18,032
Truce?

366
00:35:19,660 --> 00:35:21,327
Hey, boys.

367
00:35:27,042 --> 00:35:32,297
The ship went down in 1827
on the way to Isola del Garda

368
00:35:32,381 --> 00:35:36,509
Gossip has it this statue
was a gift from Count Lechi

369
00:35:36,593 --> 00:35:39,762
to his lover,
contralto Adelaide Malanotte.

370
00:35:42,182 --> 00:35:46,561
There are four known sets,
after the Praxiteles originals.

371
00:35:46,645 --> 00:35:48,187
This fellow's at number three.

372
00:35:48,272 --> 00:35:50,857
The Emperor Hadrian had a pair,
dug up at Tivoli,

373
00:35:50,941 --> 00:35:54,861
but one of the more philistine
of the Farnese Popes melted them down

374
00:35:54,945 --> 00:35:58,781
and had them recast as a
particularly voluptuous Venus.

375
00:36:19,345 --> 00:36:22,680
Who'd like to go for a swim
before we head back?

376
00:36:22,765 --> 00:36:28,061
We're all such pros. If I got my own
statue, it would probably be on there.

377
00:36:34,943 --> 00:36:36,569
Elio!

378
00:36:36,653 --> 00:36:38,613
Oliver!

379
00:36:42,034 --> 00:36:43,951
- I have to go. I have to go.
- Hey! Hey!

380
00:36:44,036 --> 00:36:45,745
I have to go.

381
00:36:47,539 --> 00:36:49,082
Goodness.

382
00:36:52,878 --> 00:36:55,171
- Are you going, too?
- No, no.

383
00:36:55,255 --> 00:36:57,340
I should stay
and do some work on my book.

384
00:36:57,424 --> 00:37:00,009
Come on. How about a drink
to celebrate the day?

385
00:37:00,803 --> 00:37:03,304
- Okay, maybe just one.
- All right!

386
00:37:14,566 --> 00:37:16,025
Marzia?

387
00:38:20,674 --> 00:38:23,634
The Cosmic Fragments by Heraclitus.

388
00:38:31,852 --> 00:38:35,104
The meaning of the river flowing
is not that all things are changing

389
00:38:35,189 --> 00:38:37,190
so that we cannot encounter them twice,

390
00:38:37,274 --> 00:38:40,401
but that some things
stay the same only by changing.

391
00:39:28,283 --> 00:39:31,035
Sorry, Elio.
I brought some clean clothes.

392
00:39:36,124 --> 00:39:37,583
Leave the door open.

393
00:39:38,710 --> 00:39:40,378
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

394
00:42:29,172 --> 00:42:31,090
Darling, have you seen my Heptaméron?

395
00:42:34,219 --> 00:42:35,344
Mafalda.

396
00:42:40,183 --> 00:42:41,642
It's in German.

397
00:42:43,854 --> 00:42:44,895
Okay.

398
00:42:47,649 --> 00:42:51,444
I can't remember where we left off,
but I think you'll like this one.

399
00:42:54,698 --> 00:42:56,615
Come here, darling.

400
00:42:58,577 --> 00:43:00,369
So, I'll translate, huh?

401
00:43:09,629 --> 00:43:13,799
"A handsome young knight
is madly in love with a princess.

402
00:43:13,967 --> 00:43:15,885
"And she, too, is in love with him,

403
00:43:17,220 --> 00:43:20,598
"though she seems not to be
entirely aware of it.

404
00:43:21,641 --> 00:43:23,392
"Despite the friendship..."

405
00:43:25,854 --> 00:43:28,981
"...that blossoms between them,

406
00:43:30,025 --> 00:43:32,902
"or perhaps because of
that very friendship,

407
00:43:34,112 --> 00:43:36,489
"the young knight finds himself so..."

408
00:43:39,701 --> 00:43:41,994
"...so humbled and speechless

409
00:43:42,954 --> 00:43:47,082
"that he's totally unable to bring up
the subject of his love.

410
00:43:47,959 --> 00:43:51,670
"Till one day, he asks the princess
point-blank..."

411
00:44:03,016 --> 00:44:05,184
"Is it better to speak or to die?"

412
00:44:10,565 --> 00:44:13,609
I'd never have the courage
to ask a question like that.

413
00:44:15,195 --> 00:44:16,445
I doubt that.

414
00:44:21,201 --> 00:44:23,577
Hey, Elly-Belly.

415
00:44:25,372 --> 00:44:27,540
You do know that
you can always talk to us.

416
00:44:34,214 --> 00:44:37,299
My mom's been reading
this 16th-century French romance.

417
00:44:37,425 --> 00:44:39,677
She read some of it to my dad and I
the day the lights went out.

418
00:44:40,554 --> 00:44:43,138
Yeah, about the knight that doesn't know
whether to speak or die?

419
00:44:43,223 --> 00:44:44,306
Right.

420
00:44:45,559 --> 00:44:46,976
So, does he or doesn't he?

421
00:44:48,979 --> 00:44:50,771
"Better to speak," she said.

422
00:44:52,732 --> 00:44:54,483
But she's on her guard.

423
00:44:55,861 --> 00:44:57,778
She senses a trap somewhere.

424
00:45:04,744 --> 00:45:06,036
So, does he speak?

425
00:45:07,289 --> 00:45:08,372
No.

426
00:45:10,667 --> 00:45:11,792
He fudges.

427
00:45:13,879 --> 00:45:16,255
It figures. He's French.

428
00:45:22,512 --> 00:45:24,889
I gotta go to town in a little bit
to pick some things up.

429
00:45:24,973 --> 00:45:28,434
I can go. I'm not doing anything today.

430
00:45:29,728 --> 00:45:31,186
Then why don't we go together?

431
00:45:31,271 --> 00:45:32,438
Right now?

432
00:45:32,522 --> 00:45:34,732
Yeah. Right now.

433
00:45:35,775 --> 00:45:38,193
That is, of course, unless you have
more important business going on.

434
00:45:38,278 --> 00:45:40,613
"That is, of course, unless you have
more important business going on."

435
00:45:52,959 --> 00:45:53,959
Mind if I put this in your bag?

436
00:45:54,044 --> 00:45:55,044
Yes, please.

437
00:46:06,139 --> 00:46:08,140
I straightened the wheels
and inflated the tires.

438
00:46:08,224 --> 00:46:09,642
Perfect. Thanks.

439
00:46:11,811 --> 00:46:16,190
I fell. I was coming home the other day,
and I scraped myself pretty badly.

440
00:46:16,483 --> 00:46:19,068
Anchise insisted on applying
some sort of witches' brew.

441
00:46:19,277 --> 00:46:20,694
I think it helped.

442
00:46:45,053 --> 00:46:46,428
Hold this for a second, will you?

443
00:47:06,324 --> 00:47:07,658
- Want one?
- Sure.

444
00:47:32,517 --> 00:47:33,600
Not bad, huh?

445
00:47:34,394 --> 00:47:35,519
Not bad at all.

446
00:47:38,565 --> 00:47:39,857
I thought you didn't smoke.

447
00:47:41,484 --> 00:47:42,568
I don't.

448
00:47:48,199 --> 00:47:51,201
- So, World War II, huh?
- No. This is World War I.

449
00:47:51,995 --> 00:47:54,455
You'd have to be at least 80 years old
to have known any of them.

450
00:47:55,582 --> 00:47:57,666
I never even heard
of the Battle of Piave.

451
00:47:57,792 --> 00:48:00,419
Battle of Piave was one of the most
lethal battles of World War I.

452
00:48:01,087 --> 00:48:02,796
Hundred and seventy thousand
people died.

453
00:48:04,340 --> 00:48:06,175
Is there anything you don't know?

454
00:48:10,138 --> 00:48:11,597
I know nothing, Oliver.

455
00:48:16,686 --> 00:48:18,353
Well, you seem to know
more than anybody else around here.

456
00:48:18,438 --> 00:48:20,898
Well, if you only knew how little
I know about the things that matter.

457
00:48:24,110 --> 00:48:25,486
What things that matter?

458
00:48:32,827 --> 00:48:33,952
You know what things.

459
00:48:41,169 --> 00:48:42,503
Why are you telling me this?

460
00:48:46,966 --> 00:48:48,133
'Cause I thought you should know.

461
00:48:50,095 --> 00:48:51,887
Because you thought I should know?

462
00:48:54,682 --> 00:48:56,016
'Cause I wanted you to know?

463
00:48:59,604 --> 00:49:01,563
Because I wanted you to know.

464
00:49:05,610 --> 00:49:07,277
Because I wanted you to know.

465
00:49:12,158 --> 00:49:14,493
'Cause I wanted you to know.

466
00:49:25,421 --> 00:49:28,257
Because there's no one else
I can say this to but you.

467
00:49:35,014 --> 00:49:36,765
Are you saying
what I think you're saying?

468
00:49:44,149 --> 00:49:46,441
Don't go anywhere. Stay right here.

469
00:49:47,861 --> 00:49:49,528
You know I'm not going anywhere.

470
00:50:18,975 --> 00:50:20,517
They mixed up all of my pages.

471
00:50:20,602 --> 00:50:22,728
I'm gonna have to
retype this whole thing.

472
00:50:23,229 --> 00:50:24,563
I'm not gonna have anything to work on
this afternoon.

473
00:50:24,689 --> 00:50:26,231
This is gonna set me back a whole day.

474
00:50:27,066 --> 00:50:28,108
Damn it.

475
00:50:29,402 --> 00:50:31,320
Shouldn't have said anything.

476
00:50:31,613 --> 00:50:32,779
Just pretend you never did.

477
00:50:32,864 --> 00:50:35,115
Does that mean we're on speaking terms
but not really?

478
00:50:38,620 --> 00:50:40,954
It means we can't talk
about those kinds of things.

479
00:50:42,081 --> 00:50:43,332
Okay?

480
00:50:45,084 --> 00:50:46,293
We just can't.

481
00:51:01,392 --> 00:51:02,601
Hey.

482
00:51:03,478 --> 00:51:05,354
Let's go, American!

483
00:51:26,334 --> 00:51:28,085
- Ready?
- Let's go.

484
00:52:03,746 --> 00:52:04,871
Pretty much.

485
00:52:13,172 --> 00:52:14,673
Oh, my God.

486
00:52:15,133 --> 00:52:16,800
- Thirsty?
- Yeah.

487
00:52:19,095 --> 00:52:20,679
Good morning, ma'am.

488
00:52:22,265 --> 00:52:23,557
Excuse me.

489
00:52:24,475 --> 00:52:27,185
Could I ask for a glass of water?

490
00:52:37,905 --> 00:52:39,197
Il Duce.

491
00:52:39,282 --> 00:52:41,074
"People of Italy!"

492
00:52:42,327 --> 00:52:43,577
That's Italy.

493
00:52:47,540 --> 00:52:49,082
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

494
00:53:27,914 --> 00:53:28,914
Come on!

495
00:53:50,937 --> 00:53:53,355
This is my spot. It's all mine.

496
00:53:55,358 --> 00:53:56,691
Come here to read.

497
00:53:58,152 --> 00:54:00,112
Can't tell you the number of books
I've read here.

498
00:54:02,824 --> 00:54:05,200
Oh, my God, it's freezing.

499
00:54:06,160 --> 00:54:07,786
Spring is in the mountains.

500
00:54:08,621 --> 00:54:10,038
The Alpi Orobie.

501
00:54:11,374 --> 00:54:12,749
The water comes
straight down from there.

502
00:54:39,068 --> 00:54:40,944
I like the way you say things.

503
00:54:41,028 --> 00:54:43,196
I don't know why you're always
putting yourself down, though.

504
00:54:43,656 --> 00:54:45,657
So you won't, I guess.

505
00:54:49,996 --> 00:54:51,997
You really that afraid of what I think?

506
00:55:04,927 --> 00:55:06,470
You're making things
very difficult for me.

507
00:55:19,609 --> 00:55:21,151
I love this, Oliver.

508
00:55:27,033 --> 00:55:28,033
What?

509
00:55:32,371 --> 00:55:33,497
Everything.

510
00:55:38,544 --> 00:55:39,920
Us, you mean?

511
00:55:41,797 --> 00:55:43,048
It's not bad.

512
00:55:44,133 --> 00:55:45,175
It's not bad.

513
00:56:40,147 --> 00:56:41,231
Better now?

514
00:56:49,824 --> 00:56:51,866
No, no, no.

515
00:56:52,952 --> 00:56:54,578
- We should go.
- Why?

516
00:56:55,121 --> 00:56:57,956
I know myself. Okay?
And we've been good.

517
00:56:58,040 --> 00:56:59,291
We haven't done anything
to be ashamed of,

518
00:56:59,375 --> 00:57:00,667
and that's a good thing.

519
00:57:01,294 --> 00:57:02,460
I wanna be good.

520
00:57:03,212 --> 00:57:04,212
Okay?

521
00:57:11,137 --> 00:57:12,846
Am I offending you?

522
00:57:19,729 --> 00:57:20,895
Just don't.

523
00:57:28,029 --> 00:57:30,196
I think it's starting to get infected.

524
00:57:32,158 --> 00:57:33,825
We can stop by the pharmacist's
on the way back.

525
00:57:34,410 --> 00:57:35,827
Excellent idea.

